data.content:
Danh từ
(từ Mỹ slingshot) súng cao su
máy phóng máy bay (trên tàu sân bay)
(sử học) máy lăng đá
Động từ
phóng bằng máy phóng
hất mạnh
in the crash, the driver [was] catapulted through the windscreen
trong vụ đụng xe, người lái bị hất ra ngoài qua kính chắn gió

noun
plural -pults
[count] an ancient weapon used for throwing large rocks
b Brit :slingshot
a device for launching an airplane from the deck of an aircraft carrier
verb
-pults; -pulted; -pulting
[+ obj] :to throw (something) with a catapult
They catapulted rocks toward the castle.
[+ obj] :to cause (someone or something) to quickly move up or ahead or to a better position
The publicity catapulted her CD to the top of the charts.
The novel catapulted him from unknown to best-selling author.
[no obj] :to quickly move up or ahead :to quickly advance to a better position
He catapulted to fame after his first book was published.
Her career was catapulting ahead.
